turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, the real cause of that row was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You knew there was nothing in that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort. You took presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Presents? It was only a small trivial little broach.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I remember it well. Bristling with diamonds. In the worst possible taste.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not at all. It was very pretty. And I wear it all the time. I still have it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, I didn't. You made that up all in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must admit that he was in love with you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just a little perhaps, but it was nothing serious.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You let him kiss you. You said so.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, what of it?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh come on, it gave him a lot of pleasure and it didn't harm me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, if you hadn't been so suspicious and nosey you'd have never known anything about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's a nice point of view, I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, it's true.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Are you bored with this conversation?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I definitely, most definitely am.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So am I. Bored stiff. Want some brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, thanks.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll have a little, I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see why you want it; you've already had two glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No particular reason. Anyhow, they were very small ones.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see what's the point of going on and on about something like this.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, my-you can hardly call three minute liquor glasses in the evening going on and on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's become a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You needn't be so grand just because you don't happen to want some yourself at the moment.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be so stupid.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Really, Amanda.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nothing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Going somewhere, dear?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No. Just making myself fascinating for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That reply has broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's a woman's job to allure the man. Watch me, won't you, a minute?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, that's perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, it isn't.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, it's not. I don't care.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's a pity you didn't have more brandy. It might have made you a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, it didn't seem to do such wonders with you, now did it?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, snap, snap, snap, like a little adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Adders don't snap, they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, they do. They have a big bag of venom behind their fangs and they snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't care. I don't care, do you understand? I don't care if they bark, if they roll over on the floor like hoops.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Uhh,

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: did you see much of Peter Burden after our divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I did, quite a lot actually.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I imagine that you let him kiss you quite a bit more then, didn't you?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Mind your business.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You had a riotous-must have had a riotous time. No restraint at all. Very enjoyable. You never had much anyhow.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You are quite insufferable. I suppose it's because you're drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm not in the least bit drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You've always had a weak head.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Okay. As I mentioned before, I said I had three very minute liquor glasses. That's hardly enough to get a child of two drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: On the contrary, a child of two can get violently drunk on only one glass of brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, very interesting indeed. How about a child of four or a child of six or a child of nine. We might have a splendid little debate about this intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Do shut up. Shut up.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't want to talk about this anymore.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You better turn that off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's very late and it will annoy the people upstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There aren't any people upstairs. It's a photographer's studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, I suppose the people downstairs then.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They're away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: This is no time of the year for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again, please.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No, I will do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You've always had far too temperamental for yourself. You should try to control it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I will not. Go away. Go away. I hate you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, very amusing, indeed. Amanda, listen-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Listen, indeed. No, no, no, no. I am sick and tired of listening to you, you sadistic bully.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very amusing indeed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Stop it, stop it, I hate you, I loath you, you are overbearing and conceited and utterly impossible.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You know, you're a vile, ill-tempered, wicked little beast and I hope that I never see you again as long as I live.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: This is the end. Do you hear? The end. Now and forever.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No, you're not going out like this. No you're not.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, yes I am.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes I am. Let go of me. I hate you and I loath you. God, I can't believe I just finally realized how you are. I am never marry you. Never. Never, never, never. I would rather die in torment.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, shut up. Shut up. Shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I wouldn't marry you again if you came back crawling to me on your hands and knees because you're vile. You're a mean, evil-minded little vampire and I hope to God I never set eyes on you again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Beast or brute cad, swine beast beast brute.
